modules.description: This module implements a PostgreSQL-backed cache with functions to store, retrieve, and remove key-value pairs. It supports setting values with optional expiration and querying by key, using string-based data types. It is used to persist temporary data in a PostgreSQL database, such as session storage or intermediate computation results.

This module implements a cache storage backend using MariaDB. It provides functions to set and retrieve key-value pairs, where values can be removed by setting them to `None`. The module is used to persist cache entries in a MariaDB database and integrates with the application lifecycle through service registration.

This module provides key-value caching functionality with support for storing, retrieving, and removing values, where entries can have optional expiration. It works with string-based keys and values, allowing `None` to represent removal or absence. Concrete use cases include session storage and caching intermediate computation results in SQL databases.
